We can simplify the equation by multiplying the entire equation by $x - 1$. This allows us to get rid of the denominators and simplify the equation.
\begin{align*}
(x - 1)\left(\frac{1}{x-1} + \frac{2x}{x - 1}\right) &= 7(x - 1) \\
1 + 2x &= 7x - 7 \\
-5x &= -8 \\
x &= \frac{-8}{-5} \\
x &= \frac{8}{5}
\end{align*}
So the solution to the equation is $x = \boxed{\frac{8}{5}}$.
